Package Repository

Enum Class FileType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<FileType>
Repository.FileType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<FileType>, Constable
public enum FileType extends Enum<FileType>
The FileType enum represents different types of files used in the system.

Each enum constant is associated with a specific file name that corresponds to a particular category of data managed by the system.

Enum Constants:

  • STAFF - Represents the staff data file.
  • INVENTORY - Represents the medical inventory data file.
  • REPLENISHMENT_REQUEST - Represents the replenishment request data file.
  • PATIENT - Represents the patient data file.
  • MEDICINE - Represents the medicine data file.
  • APPOINTMENT_OUTCOME - Represents the appointment outcome data file.
  • APPOINTMENT_LIST - Represents the appointment list data file.
  • MEDICAL_RECORD - Represents the medical record data file.
  • DIAGNOSIS - Represents the diagnosis data file.
  • TREATMENT - Represents the treatment data file.

Each constant has an associated file name that is used to identify the file in the system.
